FirstScen=milan_nodes.loc[(milan_nodes['Sky View Mean'] >= .33)]
SecondScen= milan_nodes.loc[(milan_nodes['Sky View Mean'] <= .14) & (milan_nodes['Green View Mean'] <= .08)]
ThirdScen= milan_nodes.loc[(milan_nodes['Sky View Mean'] <= .14) & (milan_nodes['Green View Mean'] >= .21)]

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (8,7))
ax.scatter(FirstScen.x, FirstScen.y, zorder=1, alpha= 0.2, c='b', s=10)
ax.scatter(SecondScen.x, SecondScen.y, zorder=1, alpha= 0.2, c='r', s=10)
ax.scatter(ThirdScen.x, ThirdScen.y, zorder=1, alpha= 0.2, c='green', s=10)
ax.set_title('Plotting Spatial Data for the three scenarios')
ax.set_xlabel("Longitude [D.D°]")
ax.set_ylabel("Latitude [D.D°]")
ax.legend(["Sky View Mean >= 0.33", "Sky View Mean <= 0.14 & Green View Mean <= 0.8", "Sky View Mean <= 0.14 & Green View Mean >= .21"], loc='center right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.7, 0.5))
ax.set_xlim(BBox[0],BBox[1])
ax.set_ylim(BBox[2],BBox[3])
ax.imshow(Milan_map, zorder=0, extent = BBox, aspect= 'equal')
plt.savefig("Milan_map_scenarios.png", dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
